## Annotation Analysis

### Compare Annotation Results

After BAKTA annotation completes, compare GFF files between samples:

```bash
# Extract unique product names from first GFF
grep -o 'product=[^;]*' /path/to/your/first.gff3 | sed 's/product=//' | sort | uniq > products_file1.txt

# Extract from second GFF
grep -o 'product=[^;]*' /path/to/your/second.gff3 | sed 's/product=//' | sort | uniq > products_file2.txt

# Find products unique to sample 1
comm -23 products_file1.txt products_file2.txt > unique_to_sample1.txt

# Find products unique to sample 2
comm -13 products_file1.txt products_file2.txt > unique_to_sample2.txt
```

> 💡 **Tip**: This comparison often reveals annotation variations that BAKTA versions may detect differently, providing richer functional insights.

